subSubSection.paragraph:
Terminalia (
Figs. 201–203
) large, brown. Cerci fused forming single, short, digitiform lobe; covered with bristles of different lengths, lacking spines. Epandrium completely divided. Right epandrial lamella subtriangular, covered with numerous bristles of different lengths and with spine-like bristles apically. Right surstylus not prominent. Left epandrial lamella fused to hypandrium, with 4 long bristles apically. Left surstylus with upper lobe large, subtriangular, almost devoid of bristles, only with 1 long bristle on lower margin basally and scattered, minute, marginal setulae. Hypandrium with 1 bristle, lacking slender apical processes. Phallus very short. Two rod-shaped apodemes.
